#########################From an Email with the helpdesk on 1/24/2012#####################
## This folowing pertains to a command that needs to be included in the following:
## tar -vxzf GeneTorrent-1.0.0.4.Ubuntu10.04.x86_64.tar.gz

Chris Wilks cwilks@soe.ucsc.edu
	
Jan 24
		
to Layla, support
Hi Layla,

try adding the following option to the GeneTorrent command you're running:
 --confDir /path/to/extracted/genetorrent/usr/share/GeneTorrent/

where it's two "-" and then the argument name "confDir" (just to be clear), and then the path to where you extracted genetorrent, appended with the internal dir structure of the genetorrent package (usr/share/GeneTorrent is where the conf files are).

Please let us know if that is helpful or you need additional support,
Thank you,
Chris Wilks
UCSC/CGHub

